examples.en: She bounced out of the chair.
The ball bounced off the post and into the goal.
She gave me a check for 20 dollars, but the check bounced, and I never got the money.
Her curls bounced as she jumped.
The ball hit the rim and bounced off.
The clerk was well bounced for his carelessness.
He bounced a 100-dollar check at the grocery store.
The ball skipped off Bonds' glove and bounced toward the fence.
Natural rubber production bounced back up to its prewar levels.
I won't go there, the bartender is drunk and I can get bounced.
Taylor was bounced from the team for assaulting another player.
Party members feel that they were bounced into accepting the policy.
The ball bounced off the wall and went flying into the garden next door.
...the dull knife just bounced off the skin of the tomato without cutting it...
